          "title": "Gemara compares chatas case where psul doesn't matter when, contradicting zerika proof",
          "display_title": "Chatas psul",
          "timestamp": "30:55"
        },
        {
          "title": "Resolution: qiblu pesulim vezarku is stock phrase, don't infer kabbalah timing",
          "display_title": "Stock phrase",
          "timestamp": "35:49"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Digression: Psul Oseh Shirayim and Types of Invalidation",
      "display_title": "Psul shirayim",
      "timestamp": "42:22",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Reish Lakish's question to Rabbi Yochanan on whether psul makes other blood shirayim",
          "display_title": "Reish Lakish q",
          "timestamp": "42:22"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Yochanan: only pigul and chutz limkomo make other blood shirayim, meratzeh concept",
          "display_title": "Yochanan answer",
          "timestamp": "42:51"
        },
        {
          "title": "Objection: if pigul works, why not other psul? Rabbi Zeira clarifies non-meratzeh vs meratzeh",
          "display_title": "Objection clarify",
          "timestamp": "45:06"
        },
        {
          "title": "Resolution: pigul and tamei (when overridden b'tzibbur) can make shirayim; other psulim cannot",
          "display_title": "Pigul tamei",
          "timestamp": "45:23"
        },
        {
          "title": "Explanation: tamei is sometimes permitted b'tzibbur, so its avoda quasi-valid for shirayim",
          "display_title": "Tamei b'tzibbur",
          "timestamp": "46:37"
        },
        {
          "title": "Synthesis: parallel concepts—pigul via meratzeh and tamei via hutra—both affect shirayim status",
          "display_title": "Meratzeh hutra",
          "timestamp": "48:40"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Return to Main Question: Braisa on Pigul and the Meaning of L'olam",
      "display_title": "Braisa l'olam",
